The paper analyzes the structure of computer science literature using citation analysis, which is a common method in information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL). The paper also mentions constructing article level clusters based on subject categories, which suggests a focus on database (DB) and natural language processing (CL). Additionally, the paper discusses cross-category clusters, which could relate to computer security (CR).
